The Food Standards Agency has launched an unprecedented probe into how a potentially cancer-causing dye contaminated at least 474 products.
Determined to find out how traces of the illegal dye Sudan 1 found its way into Britain's food chain, the said it was conducting its largest ever investigation with the help of five local authorities.
The Food Standards Agency sparked an international food safety alert on Feb. 18 when it announced that a sauce contaminated with the dye had been used in hundreds of British foods and exported to several European and Caribbean countries and to North America.
